A material issue not highlighted in the report has surfaced: the main evaluation routine always switches the evaluation environment to the hardest curriculum stage (`STAGES[-1]`), even while training remains at stage 0. I’m separating “hard-stage evaluation success” from the actual stage-0 rolling training record before judging the flat curves; otherwise the evidence can be misread. I’m also quantifying the initial-distance distribution and reward components rather than accepting “negligible beyond 0.15–0.25 m” qualitatively.
